### ğŸ”¹ **9. Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)**

```python
class Person:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def greet(self):
        print(f"Hi, I'm {self.name}")

p = Person("Alice")
p.greet()
```

